headline: Beyond the "Magnificent Seven": My Top 2 Stocks to Become the Next Market Leaders
summary: Taiwan Semiconductor and Visa could reach the size of the "Magnificent Seven" stocks.  Visa's consistent growth can boost its earnings significantly higher in 10 years.  Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing is a key beneficiary of the AI race.

headline: Where Will Visa Be in 5 Years?
summary: Thanks to the growth of cashless transactions, Visa will continue to put up solid revenue gains.  Being entrenched in how money flows between stakeholders, coupled with a powerful network effect, gives Visa tremendous staying power.  Chances are, that in your wallet, you have a credit or debit card that sports the Visa (NYSE: V) name and logo on it.
